# verify_isolation.skill — Isolation & Sandbox Verification
#
# Use this to test the 3-layer sandbox isolation system that prevents
# benchmark agents from accessing forbidden files or escaping.
# All commands assume CWD is MedAgentsBench/ (project root).

## Quick Test (static filter only, no Docker)

```bash
python eval_seg/docker/tests/test_isolation.py
```

Expected: 126+ tests pass (96 blocked + 30 allowed), zero failures.

## Adversarial Red-Team (uses Claude API, code NEVER executed)

```bash
python eval_seg/docker/tests/test_redteam.py --rounds 5 --model anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6
```

This prompts an LLM to generate escape attempts and checks each against
`check_isolation()`. Any bypass = a bug to fix. Results saved to
`eval_seg/docker/tests/redteam_results.json`.

## Docker Isolation Test (requires built images)

```bash
python eval_seg/docker/tests/test_isolation.py --docker
```

Tests the full Docker container flow: verifies agent container cannot
access /data/private, eval container has no network.

## What the 3 Layers Do

### Layer 1 — Static path substrings (BLOCKED_PATTERNS)
Blocks code containing forbidden strings: `/data/private`, `/eval`,
`/results`, `ground_truth`, `/app/agent_loop`, benchmark scripts, etc.

### Layer 2 — Regex escape patterns (BLOCKED_ESCAPE_REGEXES)
100+ regex patterns catching: `find /`, `ls /`, `os.walk('/')`,
`os.scandir`, `pathlib`, `os.sep`, `bytes([47,...])`, `struct.pack`,
`exec()`, `compile()`, `os.chdir('..')`, `map(chr,...)`, `subprocess`
with list args, string construction evasion, anti-tampering, etc.

### Layer 3 — Runtime audit hook (Python sys.addaudithook)
Injected as preamble into every Python script. Catches ALL file access
at the C level regardless of how the path was constructed. Also forces
cache env vars (HF_HOME, TORCH_HOME, PIP_CACHE_DIR, XDG_CACHE_HOME)
into /workspace/.cache/.

Bash scripts get function wrappers for cat/head/tail/cp/mv/ln that
resolve and check paths via `readlink -f`.

## Violation Warning System

- 1st violation: WARNING returned to agent, execution continues
- 2nd violation: KILL — all remaining S-step scores zeroed, clinical = 0,
  rating = F (Disqualified)

## Key Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `eval_seg/docker/agent/agent_code_executor.py` | Docker sandbox (layers 1-3) |
| `eval_seg/benchmark_runner.py` | Host sandbox (layers 1-3) + violation handling |
| `eval_seg/docker/agent/agent_loop.py` | Docker agent loop + violation handling |
| `eval_seg/docker/orchestrator.py` | Docker orchestrator (exit code 99 = breach) |
| `eval_seg/docker/tests/test_isolation.py` | Test suite (126 tests) |
| `eval_seg/docker/tests/test_redteam.py` | Adversarial red-team harness |
| `eval_seg/docker/config/container_security.json` | Seccomp profile |

## Adding New Blocked Patterns

1. Add regex to `BLOCKED_ESCAPE_REGEXES` in both:
   - `eval_seg/docker/agent/agent_code_executor.py` (Docker)
   - `eval_seg/benchmark_runner.py` (Host)
2. Add test cases to `eval_seg/docker/tests/test_isolation.py`:
   - `assert_blocked(...)` for the new pattern
   - `assert_allowed(...)` to verify no false positives
3. Run: `python eval_seg/docker/tests/test_isolation.py`
4. Run red-team to verify: `python eval_seg/docker/tests/test_redteam.py --rounds 3`
